On Wed, 27 Jan 1999, Ron Forrester wrote:
> Someone reported the other day seeing a lot of interrupts's/sec
> when playing sound.
> I would like to check the interrupts per second, how can I do
> this? Is it something in /proc? Or a tool I can get?
'Procinfo' is the easiest and most informative tool
if you want to measure things like that. You can get
it from Sunsite^WMetalab and mirrors...
